</div> 
<p><strong>Rivers of Blood</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Katanas" href="/Katanas" target="">Katana</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Rivers of Blood</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>, and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane">Arcane</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for mid-range combat and&nbsp;it is capable of inflicting both <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Slash Damage" href="/Slash+Damage">Slash</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Pierce Damage" href="/Pierce+Damage">Pierce</a>&nbsp;attacks. The scaling was fixed in an update</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Weapon of Okina, swordsman from the Land of Reeds.<br>A cursed weapon that has felled countless men.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>When Mohg, the Lord of Blood, first felt Okina's sword, and madness, <br>upon his flesh, he had a proposal, to offer Okina the life of a demon, whose thirst would never go unsated.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Rivers of Blood in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Rivers of Blood weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bloody Finger Okina" href="/Bloody+Finger+Okina" target="">Bloody Finger Okina</a>&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Okina invades near the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Church of Repose" href="/Church+of+Repose">Church of Repose</a>, found in the Eastern region of Mountaintops of the Giants. <br>[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2762&amp;lat=-89.18&amp;lng=156.6&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2762&amp;lat=-89.18&amp;lng=156.6&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Rivers of Blood Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Corpse Piler" href="/Corpse+Piler" target="">Corpse Piler</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li>Causes&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage">Blood loss</a>&nbsp;Buildup:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage"><img title="Causes Blood Loss Buildup" src="/file/Elden-Ring/hemmorage.png" alt="hemmorage" width="18">&nbsp;(50)</a></li> 
 <li>Despite the D scaling in Arcane, the damage gain is comparable to Dex but splits more into Fire. In addition, more arcane increases bleed build up. In summary, this weapon is reasonably viable on a pure Dex or pure Arcane build.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Corpse Piler has the same animation as <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Double Slash" href="/Double+Slash" target="">Double Slash</a>, but longer range and adds more Bleed Build Up than is listed on the weapon</li> 
 <li>Corpse Piler deals both Physical and Fire Damage</li> 
 <li>Rivers of Blood is most likely inspired by Muramasa, a swordsmith in Japan from the 16th century. Legend&nbsp;says that Muramasa's swords were cursed and demonic in power, causing bloodlust to those who wield it.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
